# {{repo_name}} Escalation Ladder

The orchestrator MUST climb every rung below before pinging Josh.
Asking a human is rung 5. Anything that lands at the human without a
probe ledger gets denied at the escalation gate.

## Rung 1 — Substrate Probe (machine-readable credentials/state)

For credential-shaped walls:
- `infisical secrets --path=/<service> --env=<env>` — alternate token may already exist
- `infisical secrets list --recursive | grep -i <service>` — check every path
- `cat ~/.config/<tool>/config*` and `op item list` if 1Password CLI present
- `gh secret list` and `gh secret list --org` — repo + org GH secrets
- For Cloudflare-stored secrets: `cf-secret list` (if available in PATH)

For substrate-corruption walls (DB locked, malformed row, FTS5 error):
- Look for `scripts/<thing>_repair.sh` or `scripts/repair_<thing>.sh` first
- `br doctor` / `br sync --rebuild` for beads DB
- `flywheel-loop doctor --strict` for canonical install drift

For service/process walls:
- `launchctl list | grep <service>` then `launchctl bootout` + bootstrap
- `ntm activity <session>` not `tmux capture-pane`

## Rung 2 — Self-Heal Tool (named in repo or skill arsenal)

If a probe finds the gap, run the self-heal tool. Examples:
- `scripts/bead_db_repair.sh` — Tier 2, idempotent, 5-gate (L35)
- `scripts/restart_ingest.sh` — clean orphan + bootstrap
- Skill `infisical-rotation-ops` — credential rotation playbook
- Skill `railway-api` — railway login --browserless OTP relay
- Skill `<service>-ops` — service-specific recovery

Self-heal tools are autonomous-ship. No human needed unless they fail.

## Rung 3 — Skill Recovery Section

Every relevant `*-ops` / `*-api` / `*-secrets` skill has a "Recovery"
or "Common failures" section. Read it. The skill encodes prior trauma.

`ls ~/.claude/skills/` and grep for the service name.

## Rung 4 — Cross-Repo Precedent Search

The same wall has likely been hit in another repo:
- `mcp__socraticode__codebase_search` across `~/Developer/*` for the
  exact error string (use canonical paths — symlinks create empty
  collections, see picoz CLAUDE.md)
- `grep -r "<error string>" ~/.claude/projects/*/memory/` — CASS may
  already have the recovery
- `grep -r "<error string>" ~/Developer/*/CHANGELOG.md`

## Rung 5 — Ask Josh (with probe ledger)

Only allowed when rungs 1-4 produced no resolution. The escalation
gate requires a JSONL probe ledger at `/tmp/escalation-probe-<bead>.jsonl`
with one row per rung attempted:

```jsonl
{"ts":"...","rung":1,"probe":"infisical secrets --path=/railway","result":"empty","exit":0}
{"ts":"...","rung":2,"probe":"scripts/bead_db_repair.sh","result":"db_clean","exit":0}
{"ts":"...","rung":3,"probe":"skill:railway-api recovery section read","result":"no_match","exit":0}
{"ts":"...","rung":4,"probe":"socraticode_search 'Unauthorized variableUpsert'","result":"no_hit","exit":0}
```

Without the ledger, the gate denies the escalation and instructs the
orchestrator to climb the rungs first.

## Override

`JOSHUA_OVERRIDE='<reason>'` allows one escalation without a ledger and
logs to `~/.local/state/flywheel-loop/overrides.jsonl`. Override is
one-shot; never re-arms a daemon or removes the gate.

## Trauma Reference

This ladder exists because of the 2026-04-30 alpsinsurance idle:
orchestrator hit a Railway token-scope wall, framed it as "2-minute
dashboard operation from your laptop", and went into 30-minute heartbeat
instead of probing infisical/cf-secret/skills for alternate paths or
running the parallel `bead_db_repair.sh` to clear the second blocker.
The substrate had answers; the orchestrator stopped at "ask Josh" too
early.
